    "## ðŸ›‘ PILLAR 2: Shannon Entropy & The Math of Obfuscation
",
    "
",
    "### The Thinking
",
    "Attackers hide their code using Base64 or custom encryption to bypass antivirus. Normal English (and normal code) has a predictable structure. Encrypted/Compressed data looks random. 
",
    "
",
    "### The Math
",
    "**Shannon Entropy** measures the "uncertainty" or "randomness" in a string of data. It ranges from 0 to 8 (for 8-bit characters).
",
    "- **Low Entropy (~3-4):** Normal English/Admin commands.
",
    "- **High Entropy (>5):** Base64 encoded blobs, encrypted payloads, or compressed malware.
",
    "
",
    "**Task:** Compare a standard admin command vs. an obfuscated one."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import math
",
    "
",
    "def shannon_entropy(data):
",
    "    if not data: return 0
",
    "    entropy = 0
",
    "    for x in range(256):
",
    "        p_x = float(data.count(chr(x))) / len(data)
",
    "        if p_x > 0:
",
    "            entropy += - p_x * math.log(p_x, 2)
",
    "    return entropy
",
    "
",
    "normal_cmd = "Get-Service | Where-Object {$_.Status -eq 'Running'}"
",
    "obfuscated_cmd = "aHR0cHM6Ly9tYWx3YXJlLWNvbnRyb2wtc2VydmVyLmNvbS9wYXlsb2Fk"
",
    "
",
    "print(f"Normal Entropy: {shannon_entropy(normal_cmd):.2f}")
",
    "print(f"Obfuscated Entropy: {shannon_entropy(obfuscated_cmd):.2f}")"
   ]
  },
